Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges. Peel @garlic{1%clove} and place
in the center of a small piece of #foil{}; drizzle with @oil{} and season with
@salt{}. Cinch into a packet. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}.

Cut @broccoli florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of oil, half the
@Fry Seasoning{1/2%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Place garlic foil packet
on same sheet.

Roast on top rack until potatoes are browned and crispy and garlic is softened,
~{20-25%minutes} for potatoes and ~{15-20%minutes} for garlic.

> Swap in broccoli for potatoes; roast 18-20 minutes.

Meanwhile, heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{5%teaspoon} in a #large pan{}
over medium-high heat. Add onion; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned
and softened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Stir in @sugar{1%teaspoon} and a splash of water; cook until onion is
caramelized and jammy, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #medium bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

While onion cooks, in a #large bowl{}, combine @ground beef{10%ounce},
remaining @Fry Seasoning{1/2%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Form into two patties, each slightly wider than a burger bun.

Once onion is done, heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat.
Add patties and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

In the last ~{1-2%minutes} of cooking, top patties with
@Swiss cheese{2%slice}; cover pan to melt cheese.

While patties cook, carefully unwrap foil packet; mash roasted garlic with
a #fork{} or finely chop.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{4%tablespoon}, roasted garlic, and
@wasabi paste{1%teaspoon} to taste. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> TIP: Start with half the wasabi, then taste and add more from there if you like.

Halve and toast @potato buns{2}.

Spread bottom buns with as much aioli as you like (save a bit for dipping if
desired). Fill buns with patties and caramelized onion.

Divide burgers and potato wedges between plates. Serve any remaining aioli on
the side.

> TIP: If you have ketchup on hand, serve some on the side for dipping.